the golden quadrilateral connecting the four largest cities of chennai, mumbai, delhi and kolkata with four-laned highways has been completed and is of a reasonable standard. some of it is of an international standard but that cannot be said for all of it. however, improving the quality of the roads does not improve the way in which people drive and it is very dangerous to drive on the roads in india as people drive as they like without regard to any rules (rules do exist but are almost never enforced). hiring driver with car[edit] instead, if you desire going by 